<div class="content">
<h1>Why It Makes Sense to Bite the Hand that Feeds You</h1>

<p><a href="http://www.errolmorris.com/content/reexaminations/reexaminations1.html">Errol Morris</a>:</p>

<blockquote>
  <ol>
  <li><p>Preventive bite. Hand is bound to betray you eventually. Get it before it gets you. Remember, every hand is capable of naked aggression.</p></li>
  <li><p>Preemptive bite. Hand is ready to do something. Just look at it. You&#8217;ve got to protect yourself, don&#8217;t you?</p></li>
  <li><p>Keeps gums healthy.</p></li>
  <li><p>Hand less likely poisoned than food.</p></li>
  <li><p>Tastes good.</p></li>
  <li><p>Why not&#8230;?</p></li>
  </ol>
</blockquote>


<p><i>You should follow me on twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/aaronsw">here</a>.</i></p>
<p class="posted">November 27, 2006</p>

